- TRACE: No

- DELETE: Yes

Explanation:
- The method editPrintShopReview is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{printShopId}/reviews/{reviewId}", method = RequestMethod.PUT), so PUT is explicitly accepted for that exact path.
- The method deletePrintShopReview is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{printShopId}/reviews/{reviewId}", method = RequestMethod.DELETE), so DELETE is also explicitly accepted for the same path.
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping in this controller, so no additional prefix applies; the full path is exactly as in the method annotations.
- No @RequestMapping for this path is present with other HTTP methods (GET, POST, PATCH, OPTIONS, TRACE, HEAD), so based on the source code only PUT and DELETE are acceptable. (Per the instruction, I did not assume framework-provided implicit handling such as automatic HEAD/OPTIONS.)
